---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro'
import LegalPage from '@/components/LegalPage.astro'

const title = 'Terms of Service - GK Vip Transfer Kos'
const description =
    'Booking terms for GK Vip Transfer on Kos: confirmation via WhatsApp, fixed prices paid after the ride, changes and cancellations, luggage, and liability.'
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} lang="en" pageType="legal">
  <LegalPage lang="en" heading="Terms of Service" updated="12 July 2026" altHref="/el/terms/">
    <h2>The service</h2>
    <p>
      GK Vip Transfer, operated by Georgia Kommata on Kos island, Greece, provides pre-booked
      private transfers between Kos International Airport (KGS), Kos Port, hotels and resorts across
      the island, as well as private island tours. By booking a transfer you agree to these terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Bookings and confirmation</h2>
    <p>
      You can request a booking through the website form, WhatsApp, or phone. A booking is confirmed
      only when we reply to you on WhatsApp or by phone. Please make sure the details you give us,
      especially your flight number, pickup time, and location, are accurate; we rely on them to
      have your driver in the right place at the right time.
    </p>

    <h2>Prices and payment</h2>
    <p>
      Every ride has a fixed price agreed at the time of booking, with no hidden fees. Payment is
      made at the end of the ride, in cash (EUR) or by card. We do not take prepayments.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes and cancellations</h2>
    <p>
      If your plans change, tell us as early as possible on WhatsApp or by phone and we will
      reschedule or cancel your booking. Since we take no prepayment, there is nothing to refund.
    </p>

    <h2>Flights and pickup</h2>
    <p>
      We track your flight and adjust the pickup time to the actual arrival, so a flight delay does
      not change the agreed price. If you cannot locate your driver at the meeting point, call or
      message us on WhatsApp at +30 697 296 1560 immediately and we will guide you.
    </p>

    <h2>Luggage</h2>
    <p>
      The agreed price includes luggage within the vehicle's stated capacity (up to 3 large
      suitcases in the sedan, up to 6 in the van). Please tell us in advance about oversized or
      special items, such as sports equipment or mobility aids, so we can plan the right vehicle.
    </p>

    <h2>Passenger conduct</h2>
    <p>
      Seat belts are required by Greek law for all passengers. Smoking is not permitted in the
      vehicles. The driver may refuse or end a ride if passenger behaviour puts safety at risk.
    </p>

    <h2>Liability</h2>
    <p>
      Transfers are performed with licensed, insured vehicles and drivers in accordance with Greek
      law. We are not liable for delays or losses caused by events outside our reasonable control,
      such as extreme traffic, weather, or force majeure. When booking a transfer to the airport or
      port, please allow enough time for check-in and boarding.
    </p>

    <h2>Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These terms are governed by Greek law. Any dispute falls under the jurisdiction of the courts
      of Kos, Greece.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      GK Vip Transfer, Kos, Greece. Email <a data-email-user="gkommata" data-email-domain="gmail.com">gkommata [at] gmail [dot] com</a>,
      phone and WhatsApp +30 697 296 1560.
    </p>
  </LegalPage>
</Layout>
